{"A solid and eventful quarter": "KONGSBERG is well-positioned, has a record-high order backlog, and market activity has never been higher. This provides a solid foundation for further growth."}
{"Highlights in the quarter": "Martime"}
{"Financial": "\u00b7 Positive growth in both EBIT and EBIT margin. Generally good and efficient project execution"}
{"Market and order intake": "KONGSBERG has high growth ambitions for Kongsberg Digital, and significant investments are being made in scaling and rolling out new solutions and applications."}
{"Other": "\u00d8vrige"}
{"Key figures": "4) 12-month rolling EBITDA"}
{"Performance and order intake": "The order backlog at the end of Q3 2024 was MNOK 96 865 , an increase of MNOK 1 304 in the quarter and MNOK 27 632 since Q3 2023."}

{"Cash flow": "So far this year, KONGSBERG has had a net increase in cash and cash equivalents of MNOK 1 151. The largest increase came from positive EBITDA and positive  working capital development. The largest outgoing cash flows were related to dividend payments, repayment of KOG13 bond and investments in production facilities and associated equipment."}

{"Balance sheet": "KONGSBERG has a long-term issuer rating of A- with a \u00abstable prospect\u00bb awarded by the credit rating agency Nordic Credit Rating. The standalone credit assessment is BBB+. The rating was last updated on 19 April 2024 and can be found on www.nordiccreditrating.com."}

{"Product development": "In addition, customer-financed development, either as part of a project or as a specified development assignment. The total scope of product development and maintenance accounts for about ten per cent of operating revenues over time."}
{"Employees": "Kongsberg Digital"}

{"Order backlog": "37%"}

{"Results": "EBIT was MNOK 167 in 3rd quarter, corresponding to an EBIT margin of 14,9 per cent compared to MNOK 149 (16,1 per cent)  in the same quarter last year. The margin change from Q3 last year is mainly due to a different project mix. Accumulated so far in 2024, EBIT was MNOK 424, up from MNOK 407 in 2023."}
{"Market and orders": "At the end of Q3 2024, Kongsberg Maritime had an order backlog of MNOK 20 536."}
{"Other conditions": "The transaction is expected to be completed no later than Q1 2025."}

{"Resultat": "EBIT in the quarter was MNOK (43) compared to MNOK (84) same quarter last year. The negative operating profit was due to investments in product development and sales and marketing activities. Accumulated EBIT in Q3 2024 was MNOK (261) compared to MNOK (326) in the same period 2023."}
{"Market and Orders": "At the end of Q3 2024, Kongsberg Discovery had an order backlog of  MNOK 3 002."}
{"Increased missile capacity": "KONGSBERG already has contracts for deliveries of both missile variants to both the USA and Australia."}

{"Other factors": "Kongsberg Defence & Aerospace has almost half of its order backlog hedged against inflation through escalation clauses in its contracts.
